<item>
            <title>[LU-6871] Clean up data structure client_bd</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6871</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Now client_obd data structure includes fields exclusively used by MGC, MDC, and OSC specifically, which makes this structure huge and hard to understand. It&apos;s reasonable to split those fields and have individual data structure for MGC, MDC, and OSC.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In order to avoid excessive code changes, it&apos;s reasonable to have the following  definition:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;struct client_obd_osc {
    struct client_obd osc_cli;
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;/* OSC fields */&lt;/span&gt;
};

struct client_obd_mgc {
    struct client_obd mgc_cli;
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;/* mgc fields */&lt;/span&gt;
};

...
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This way the common code to handle client_obd connecting or disconnecting are still usable.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
